  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 275°F (135°C).",
    "Score the pork belly in a crisscross pattern and rub with olive oil, garlic, rosemary, salt, and black pepper.",
    "Place the pork belly in a roasting pan and bake for 2 hours, or until tender and caramelized.",
    "Remove the pork belly from the oven and let it rest for 10 minutes before slicing.",
    "Serve the sliced pork belly with crusty bread and a squeeze of lemon juice.",
